
[1]hiatus

   HIA'TUS, n. [L. from hio, to open or gape.]

   1. An opening; an aperture; a gap; a chasm.

   2. The opening of the mouth in reading or speaking, when a word ends
   with a vowel,and the following word begins with a vowel.

   3. A defect; a chasm in a manuscript,where some part is lost or
   effaced.
